Followed steps from
   https://www.freakyjolly.com/angular-7-6-crud-operations-using-firebase-and-firestore-database-in-angular-application-tutorial/
   
1. Got to https://firebase.google.com/  and click on getting started -> in next page -> click on "Add Project" 
-> entered "angular crud" -> click "continue" -> Register a Web App -> enter name "angular crud" -> Pickup 
the details from Add Firebase SDK and add it in environments -> environment.ts file.

export const environment = {
    production: false,
    firebase: {
      apiKey: "",
      authDomain: "",
      databaseURL: "",
      projectId: "",
      storageBucket: "",
      messagingSenderId: ""
    }
   };
   

   
 2. go to local angular project 
   D:\angular\angularcrud> npm install --save firebase @angular/fire
   
 follow rest from   https://www.freakyjolly.com/angular-7-6-crud-operations-using-firebase-and-firestore-database-in-angular-application-tutorial/
